### ============================================================================
### service-policy — FULL LIFECYCLE walkthrough (create → version → activate →
### evaluate → deactivate), with request AND response contracts for each step.
###
### Open in VS Code (REST Client) or IntelliJ HTTP Client; run top-down.
### Start the app first:  ./mvnw quarkus:dev    (Docker running for MongoDB + OIDC)
### Swagger UI: http://localhost:8080/q/swagger-ui   OpenAPI: /q/openapi
###
### Tokens (ADR-013):
###   {{admin_jwt}} — token whose role/scope satisfies the admin marker
###                   (default role "authz-admin"). Required for all /v1/policies* writes.
###   {{jwt}}       — any valid authenticated token. Used for /v1/evaluate.
###   See "How to obtain tokens" at the bottom.
###
### KEY CONCEPTS you'll exercise:
###   - `app` is REQUIRED (ADR-024). A policy belongs to exactly one application, and
###     evaluation is scoped by (app, resourceType): a policy of app-a can NEVER decide
###     a request of app-b. No wildcard, no "global" scope.
###     `resourceType` is a per-app namespace — use "document", NOT "rh:document".
###   - Create leaves the policy INACTIVE. It is NOT evaluable until you activate it.
###   - Versions are append-only (PUT adds v2, v3…); you activate an EXPLICIT version.
###   - Writes are conditional: they need If-Match: "<revision>" (the ETag from a GET).
###       Stale ETag → 412 ; missing If-Match → 428.
###   - The listing shows ALL lifecycle states by default (ADR-025); ?status= filters.
###   - Errors are RFC 9457 application/problem+json (see docs/ERRORS.md).
### ============================================================================

@host = http://localhost:8080
@auth_admin = Bearer {{admin_jwt}}
@auth = Bearer {{jwt}}


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) CREATE a policy  →  201 Created, INACTIVE
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "policyId": "doc-access",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [
    { "id": "assigned-access", "effect": "PERMIT",
      "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "IN",
        "left": {"ref": "subject.id"}, "right": {"ref": "resource.attr.assignees"} } }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  201 Created
### { "policyId": "doc-access", "version": 1, "active": false }
###                                            ↑ created inactive; not evaluable yet


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) LIST — the freshly created (INACTIVE) policy is visible by default (ADR-025)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK   (Paginated<PolicyHeadSummary>)
### {
###   "data": [
###     { "policyId": "doc-access", "app": "rh", "resourceType": "document",
###       "activeVersion": null,      ← inactive, and still listed
###       "revision": 0, "audit": { "createdBy": "…", "createdAt": "…", "changeReason": null } }
###   ],
###   "pagination": { "page": 1, "size": 20, "totalPages": 1, "totalElements": 1 }
### }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) GET the policy  →  200, read the ETag (you need it to write)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK   (note the ETag response header)
### Headers:  ETag: "0"          ← revision counter; use it as If-Match below
### Body (PolicyHeadView):
### { "policyId": "doc-access", "app": "rh", "resourceType": "document",
###   "activeVersion": null, "revision": 0, "audit": {…}, "activeContent": null }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) APPEND a new version (PUT)  →  200, creates v2 (still inactive)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### `app` must match the policy's app — it is IMMUTABLE across versions (ADR-024).
PUT {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "0"

{
  "content": {
    "app": "rh",
    "policyId": "doc-access",
    "version": 2,
    "resourceType": "document",
    "actions": ["*"],
    "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
    "defaultEffect": "DENY",
    "rules": [
      { "id": "assigned-access", "effect": "PERMIT",
        "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "IN",
          "left": {"ref": "subject.id"}, "right": {"ref": "resource.attr.assignees"} } },
      { "id": "area-scope", "effect": "PERMIT",
        "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "EQ",
          "left": {"ref": "resource.attr.area"}, "right": {"ref": "subject.attr.area"} } }
    ]
  },
  "changeReason": "add area-scope rule"
}

### EXPECTED RESPONSE  200 OK
### Headers:  ETag: "1"          ← revision bumped 0 → 1
### Body: head view; activeVersion still null (append does not activate).


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) LIST versions  →  200, see the history
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/versions
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 OK — data: [ {policyId, app:"rh", version:1, …}, {… version:2 …} ]


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) EVALUATE before activating  →  200 allowed:false (nothing is active)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### `app` is REQUIRED on every evaluation request (ADR-024).
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  { "allowed": false, "reason": "…", "policyVersion": null, … }


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 7) ACTIVATE version 2  →  200, now it's live
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "1"

{
  "version": 2,
  "changeReason": "go live with area-scope"
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK, ETag: "2"   (activeVersion: 2, activeContent: <v2 document>)


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 8) EVALUATE — PERMIT (subject is an assignee)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Replace "test-user" with the sub in your {{jwt}}.
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: true, policyVersion: "2"


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 9) EVALUATE — PERMIT via area-scope (v2's new rule)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d2", "attributes": {"area": "A"}},
  "subjectAttributes": {"area": "A"}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: true


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 10) EVALUATE — DEFAULT DENY (nothing matches)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d4", "attributes": {"assignees": ["someone-else"], "area": "B"}},
  "subjectAttributes": {"area": "A"}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: false (defaultEffect DENY)


### ============================================================================
### APPLICATION ISOLATION (ADR-024) — the core guarantee, made tangible
### Same resourceType "document" in a different app. They never cross.
### ============================================================================

### 11) Create a policy in app "nami", SAME resourceType, opposite outcome
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "nami",
  "policyId": "doc-access-nami",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [
    { "id": "clearance-gate", "effect": "PERMIT",
      "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "EQ",
        "left": {"ref": "resource.attr.clearanceLevel"}, "right": {"value": 5} } }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED  201.  Same resourceType as the "rh" policy — no collision (ADR-024).


### 12) Activate it
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access-nami/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "0"

{ "version": 1 }

### EXPECTED  200, ETag: "1"


### 13) ISOLATION — the same body as step 8, but under app "nami" → DENIED
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "nami",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: FALSE
### The rh policy (which permits this exact request) is INVISIBLE to app "nami".


### 14) ISOLATION — the nami request under app "rh" → DENIED
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d9", "attributes": {"clearanceLevel": 5}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: FALSE  (the nami policy is invisible to app "rh")


### 15) …and under its own app, it PERMITs
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "nami",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d9", "attributes": {"clearanceLevel": 5}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: TRUE


### ============================================================================
### LISTING FILTERS — ?app= (ADR-024) + ?status= (ADR-025). They compose with AND.
### ============================================================================

### 16) All policies, all states (default)
GET {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 — both "doc-access" (rh) and "doc-access-nami" (nami)


### 17) Only active
GET {{host}}/v1/policies?status=active
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 — only heads with activeVersion != null


### 18) Only inactive
GET {{host}}/v1/policies?status=inactive
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 — only heads with activeVersion == null


### 19) Filter by app
GET {{host}}/v1/policies?app=rh
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 — only policies of app "rh"


### 20) COMPOSITION — app AND status
GET {{host}}/v1/policies?app=rh&status=active
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  200 — only the ACTIVE policies of app "rh"


### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 21) DEACTIVATE  →  200, soft retire (history intact)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/deactivate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "2"

{ "changeReason": "temporarily retire" }

### EXPECTED  200, ETag: "3".  activeVersion: null, activeContent: null (versions kept)


### 22) EVALUATE after deactivate  →  200 allowed:false
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1", "attributes": {"assignees": ["test-user"]}}
}

### EXPECTED  200 OK  →  allowed: false


### ============================================================================
### ERROR CONTRACTS — RFC 9457 application/problem+json (docs/ERRORS.md)
### ============================================================================

### 23) 400 INVALID_POLICY — create without `app` (ADR-024: required)
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "policyId": "no-app",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": []
}

### EXPECTED  400  code: "INVALID_POLICY"  (invalidParams points at 'app')


### 24) 400 INVALID_POLICY — append with a DIFFERENT app (app is immutable)
### Use the CURRENT ETag of doc-access (GET it first) in place of "3".
PUT {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "3"

{
  "content": {
    "app": "nami",
    "policyId": "doc-access",
    "version": 3,
    "resourceType": "document",
    "actions": ["*"],
    "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
    "defaultEffect": "DENY",
    "rules": []
  },
  "changeReason": "try to move it to another app"
}

### EXPECTED  400  code: "INVALID_POLICY"
### → "app is immutable; policy 'doc-access' belongs to app 'rh'".
### A policy can never be moved between applications.


### 25) 400 BAD_REQUEST — evaluate without `app`
POST {{host}}/v1/evaluate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "document:read",
  "resource": {"type": "document", "id": "d1"}
}

### EXPECTED  400  code: "BAD_REQUEST"  → "app must not be blank."
### (Same rule applies to EVERY item of /v1/evaluate/batch — a missing app fails the
###  whole batch with 400, it does not return a silent deny.)


### 26) 400 — invalid ?status= value
GET {{host}}/v1/policies?status=whatever
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  400  → "'status' must be one of: active, inactive, all."
### NOTE: ?status= (present but EMPTY) is ALSO 400 — a blank value is an explicit
### invalid value, not an absence. The default only applies when the param is omitted.


### 27) 409 POLICY_ALREADY_EXISTS
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "policyId": "doc-access",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": []
}

### EXPECTED  409  code: "POLICY_ALREADY_EXISTS"


### 28) 428 PRECONDITION_REQUIRED — write without If-Match
PUT {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "content": { "app": "rh", "policyId": "doc-access", "version": 4,
    "resourceType": "document", "actions": ["*"],
    "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES", "defaultEffect": "DENY", "rules": [] },
  "changeReason": "no if-match" }

### EXPECTED  428  code: "PRECONDITION_REQUIRED"


### 29) 412 PRECONDITION_FAILED — stale If-Match
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "0"

{ "version": 1 }

### EXPECTED  412  code: "PRECONDITION_FAILED"  (extension: currentRevision)


### 30) 404 POLICY_NOT_FOUND
GET {{host}}/v1/policies/does-not-exist
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}

### EXPECTED  404  code: "POLICY_NOT_FOUND"


### 31) 404 VERSION_NOT_FOUND — activate a version that doesn't exist
### Use the current ETag of doc-access in place of "3".
POST {{host}}/v1/policies/doc-access/activate
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json
If-Match: "3"

{ "version": 99 }

### EXPECTED  404  code: "VERSION_NOT_FOUND"


### 32) 400 INVALID_POLICY — ordering operator with a non-numeric LITERAL (ADR-023)
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth_admin}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "app": "rh",
  "policyId": "bad-typed",
  "version": 1,
  "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"],
  "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES",
  "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [
    { "id": "bad", "effect": "PERMIT",
      "condition": { "type": "comparison", "op": "GT",
        "left": {"ref": "subject.attr.clearance"}, "right": {"value": "abc"} } }
  ]
}

### EXPECTED  400  code: "INVALID_POLICY"
### NOTE (ADR-023): a non-numeric LITERAL is rejected at authoring. A non-numeric
### ATTRIBUTE resolved at runtime is NOT an error — the comparison just doesn't hold
### → deny. /evaluate never returns 500 on operand type.


### 33) 403 FORBIDDEN — write with a non-admin token
POST {{host}}/v1/policies
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "app": "rh", "policyId": "nope", "version": 1, "resourceType": "document",
  "actions": ["*"], "combiningAlgorithm": "DENY_OVERRIDES", "defaultEffect": "DENY",
  "rules": [] }

### EXPECTED  403  code: "FORBIDDEN"  (caller lacks the admin marker)


### ============================================================================
### CLEANUP — there is no hard delete by design (soft retire only).
### To reset in dev, drop the Mongo collections or use fresh policyIds.
### ============================================================================

### ============================================================================
### HOW TO OBTAIN TOKENS (dev)
### ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### In quarkus:dev the OIDC dev services start a Keycloak. Get tokens via the
### Dev UI (http://localhost:8080/q/dev) → OIDC. {{admin_jwt}} must carry the admin
### marker (role "authz-admin" by default; configurable per ADR-013). {{jwt}} is any
### authenticated user.
###
### POLICY AUTHORING REFERENCE:
###   app          REQUIRED (ADR-024). The application the policy belongs to.
###                Immutable across versions. No wildcard, no "global" scope.
###   resourceType Per-app namespace: "document", NOT "rh:document".
###   Operators:   EQ, NEQ, IN, NOT_IN, GT, GTE, LT, LTE
###   Operands:    {"ref": "<path>"}  paths: subject.id | subject.attr.* |
###                resource.type | resource.id | resource.attr.* | context.*
###            or  {"value": <literal>}
###   Composites:  {"type": "and"|"or", "conditions": [ … ]}
###   Ordering ops (GT/GTE/LT/LTE) require numeric operands (ADR-023).
### ============================================================================
